913.name: Western Wing
description: You are in the western wing of the castle.  This hallway continues to the
south, and you hear pots and pans rattling to the north.

909.name: Castle Entryway
description: You are in the entryway of a large castle.  It is very beautiful, with
large paintings and a lovely carpet.  You hear jovial laughter to the north,
while smaller corridors branch off to the east and west.

911.name: Western Wing
description: You are in the western wing of the castle.  You see the entrance to the
east, while this hallway continues to the west.

916.name: Eastern Wing
description: You are in the eastern wing of the castle.  The hall turns to the
north here, and a private room is to the east.

929.name: Guest Quarters
description: You have entered private quarters which are reserved for visitors to the
castle.  You nearly faint as you recognize the occupant of this chamber as Odin
himself, patron God of Westbridge.  He must be visiting Zeus.

938.name: Planning Room
description: You have entered a large room dominated by a huge table with a large map
on it.  Several men are gathered around the table, studying the map carefully.

907.name: Zeus Street
description: You are on the main street of this town, called Zeus street. There is some
sort of store to the west.

933.name: Stable
description: You are in the stable of the castle.  Rather than the horses which you
expected to find, it is filled with a wide variety of creatures which you
thought were mythical.  Obviously, you were wrong.

918.name: Dungeon
description: You are in Zeus's Dungeon.  You wonder what creatures are so terrible that
even mighty Zeus fears them enough to imprison them.

935.name: Armoury
description: This small store is almost empty.  It seems as if there is not much here,
but the shopkeeper doesn't want to do business with you anyways.

901.name: Mountain
description: You are climbing a large mountain which towers over Ofcol.  The path
continues up the mountain, but part of it is gone.  There is no way to
continue by land.

924.name: Bakery
description: You are in the small store which supplies the residents of this town with
their food.  It smells wonderful in here!

951.name: Swirling Corridor
description: The hallway narrows, disjoins and becomes beyond reality as the
walls melt and swirl with the tides of immortal breaths.

922.name: Cell
description: You are in a small, cramped, dirty cell.  It is a horrid place.

914.name: Kitchen
description: You have entered the kitchen of this castle, and it is a hotbed of
activity.  Servants are bustling about, preparing food for the Gods
themselves.

945.name: Bed Room
description: You are in the bed room of a God!

940.name: Northern Hall
description: You are in the northern hallway.  There is a private room to the north,
and the stairs leading down are to the south.

906.name: Zeus Street
description: You are walking down what appears to be the main street of this city.
You see large residences to the east and west, while the street continues
to the north and south.
The street continues.

928.name: Ares Street
description: You are on a smaller road which branches off from the main street.  On a
sign, you notice that the name of this road is Ares Street.

931.name: Guest Quarters
description: This room is sparsely decorated, compared to the others in this
castle.  There are several generic articles lying neatly upon the
front table: a hairbrush, a mirror, and a basket of fruit.  This seems
to be a guest room in the castle.

941.name: Southern Hall
description: You are in the southern hallway.  There is a private room to the south,
and the stairs leading down are to the north.

925.name: Residence
description: You are in the residence of one of the inhabitants of this town.  She
looks vaguely familiar, but you can't place her name ...

934.name: Ares Street
description: You have reached the end of Ares Street.  To the south you see an
armoury, while there is a weapons shop to the east.  To the north is a
lone building.

902.name: Mountain
description: You are making your way up the mountain.  The rigorous climb has left you
tired, and you are ready to take a break.

926.name: Residence
description: You are in the residence of one of the inhabitants of this town.  He looks
vaguely familiar, but you can't place his name ...

944.name: Bed Room
description: This bedroom is simple, and lacks the luxury of the others.

919.name: Dungeon
description: You are in Zeus's Dungeon.  There are cells to the north, west, and east.
From the east and west, you hear guttural noises.  From the north, nothing ...

917.name: Eastern Wing
description: You are in the eastern wing of the castle.  You hear animals to the north,
while the hallway continues to the south.

908.name: Zeus Street
description: You are still on the main thoroughfare of this town.  To the north, you see
a large castle.  To the east there is a smaller road.

921.name: Cell
description: You are in a small, cramped, dirty cell.  It is a horrid place.

946.name: Bed Room
description: You are in the bed room of a God!

912.name: Western Wing
description: You are in the western wing of the castle.  The hallway continues to the
north and private rooms to the west.

947.name: Bed Room
description: You are in the bed room of a God!

915.name: Eastern Wing
description: You are in the eastern wing of the castle.  The hall continues to the
east, while the entrance is back to the west.

923.name: Stairway
description: You have come to a large stairway leading up.  To the south, you see the
throne room of Zeus.

936.name: Weapon Shop
description: You have entered a small store with a modest selection of weapons.
You get the feeling that there is not a very wide selection here, but
it also seems that the shopkeeper is not very interested in outsiders.
To the south the sounds of hammering can be heard.

927.name: Mystic Shop
description: You are in the store which provides the citizens here with whichever
arcane objects they may need.

942.name: Western Hall
description: You are in the western hallway.  There is a private room to the west, and
the stairs leading down are to the east.

932.name: Storage Room
description: You are in a storage room of the castle.  There isn't much here, just a lot
of dust.

939.name: Second Floor
description: You are on the second floor of this castle.  You are numb from your
discoveries on the first floor, and wonder what secrets the upper floor of this
castle holds.  Hallways extend in all directions, and you see a small, closed
hatch above you.
You see a sign on the hatch.  It reads 'Private Property. No trespassing!'

943.name: Eastern Hall
description: You are in the eastern hallway.  There is a private room to the east, and
the stairs leading down are to the west.

904.name: Entrance
description: You are at the entrance to a huge city.  As you look around, you realize
that the inhabitants of this city must be very wealthy indeed - you have never
seen a city with such beautiful buildings.

910.name: Throne Room
description: You stop dead in your tracks as you enter this room.  Before you is Zeus,
in all his glory, sitting on a huge golden throne.  You had thought him to be
just a myth, but here he is ... you wonder who else lives in this castle.
This huge golden throne looks as if it has been here for ages.  As you study it
carefully, you notice that it is not firmly attached to the floor ... perhaps
you could slide it?

903.name: Mountain
description: You have finally reached the top of the mountain.  The air here is so
thin that you must gasp for breath.  To the north, you see what seems to be
the entrance to a city.  You see a path that goes east and then turns out
south to a large cliff.

920.name: Cell
description: You are in a small, cramped, dirty cell.  It is a horrid place.

937.name: Smithy
description: This large room is so noisy, you can barely hear yourself think.
All the occupants are hard at work, crafting high quality weapons and
armor.  Something is strange about the west wall, although you can't
quite tell what it is.
Upon closer inspection, cryptic text is etched upon this wall:
{x
Give her hope, life has none left
In her fleeting, wings severed and drawn
In twilight hours, mortal hearts be heft
And darkness lifting, a new saga is spun.

930.name: Storage Room
description: You are in a storage room of the castle.  There isn't much here, just a
few boxes filled with old junk.

948.name: Hall of Gods
description: You have entered the most sacred of places, the hall of true Gods.
If you This foyer marks the high mountain of the ancient gods, where
those who have long since fallen from immortal favor now reside as
king among mortals.  To the north, a swirling corridor stretches into
darkness and light.

900.name: A {wV{cist{wa {mOverlooking {xthe {BRe{bal{Bms{x
description: This magnificent vista overlooks the whole of the realms in three
directions, save the south where the swirling corridor awaits.  A
strange box lies on the floor, magnificently carved and unignorably
compelling.

905.name: Zeus Street
description: You are walking down a huge street.  You notice that there are not many
people in this town.  On a corner, you see a sign marked 'Zeus Street'.
To the west, you see a small store.
The street continues.

900.name: Epimetheus~
description:
He looks much less his brother, the philanthroper of fire, though
he seems like interested in contemplating the fate of mortals than he
does looking for something to entertain him for the moment.
900.room_name: Epimetheus is here in idle thought.

901.name: Zeus~
description:
You see before you the greatest of the Olympians.  It seems as if he could
destroy you with a thought.  Every glance penetrates deep into your soul.
You now know what true fear is.
901.room_name: Zeus sits here on a throne.

902.name: Prometheus~
description:
This mortal risked the wrath of Zeus to give the gift of fire to humans.  He
looks up at you and smiles.
902.room_name: Prometheus is here, playing with a match.

903.name: Hermes~
description:
This is the messenger of the Gods.  He wears a winged helm and boots, and
darts from place to place.  He looks very busy, and it seems as if he doesn't
even notice your presence.
903.room_name: Hermes is busy, delivering a message.

904.name: Poseidon~
description:
He is the brother of Zeus himself, chosen to rule the seas.  He must be
visiting Mount Olympus.  He nods at you and motions for you to enter and
have a seat.

905.name: Apollo~
description:
This jovial God is strumming on a lyre.  He smiles at you and asks you to
join him.  You notice a dangerous looking bow by his side, however, and think
that he knows more than music.
905.room_name: Apollo is here, playing a tune.

906.name: Ares~
description:
The God of War is here, studying some maps.  He scowls at you as you enter
and says 'I am very busy.  What do you want?'
906.room_name: Ares is here, kicking your ass.

907.name: Athena~
description:
Zeus' favorite daughter is sitting on a couch eating grapes.  She smiles at
you and invites you to join her.

908.name: Hephaestus~
description:
This god is far from being physically perfect.  He seems lame and
rather ugly, yet there is the impression of kindness about him, that
is if you are one worthy of his interest to begin with.  He seems to
have no shortage of attention, as several golden maidens of exquisite
beauty tend to his every need and desire.
908.room_name: Hephaestus the Smith is here, crafting a fine weapon.

909.name: A Golden Maiden~
description:
As you gaze upon this creation, you realize that she is made from solid
gold.  She seems to be very lifelike as she assists the smith in his work.
909.room_name: A Handmaid of gold is here, assisting the smith.

910.name: A Soldier~
description:
This man is waiting on Ares.  Although he does not look very strong, you
realize that Ares would not have any weaklings working for him.
910.room_name: A soldier is here, assisting Ares.

911.name: an apprentice musician~
description:
This man has mastered his first profession, and is now studying music from the
immortal Apollo.
911.room_name: A musician is here, learning from Apollo.

912.name: A serving boy~
description: This boy is truly lucky to be able to serve Athena herself.
912.room_name: A servant is here, feeding Athena her grapes.

913.name: A hound of war~
description:
This great beast can barely be called a dog.  It has been bred to cause fear
on the battle field, and you have no doubt that it does its job well.
913.room_name: A large hound snarls at you.

914.name: Odin~
description:
As you gaze at Odin, you realize how insignificant you truly are.  He towers
over you, and is so intent on his activities that he barely recognizes your
presence.

915.name: Julius the Green Grocer~
description:
This jovial man has devoted his life to selling fruit and other foods to the
inhabitants of this city.  Although he may seem like a wimp, it would be wise
not to underestimate him.  He smiles warmly at you and shows you his selection
of delicious looking foods.
915.room_name: Julius the Green Grocer stands here.

916.name: the Alchemist~
description:
Skilled in all manner of magic, as well as the ancient art of alchemy, he
stands ready to supply the citizens here (but not you) with all manner of
arcane supplies.
916.room_name: The ancient, wizened Alchemist stands here.

917.name: Clive the Weapons Master~
description:
Clive looks VERY big and VERY tough.  All those years in the army
must have paid off.
917.room_name: Clive the Weapons Master is practicing with his bow and axe.

918.name: Samuel the Armourer~
description:
Samuel looks just like Clive the Weapons Master: VERY big and VERY tough.
He doesn't like what you've been doing in his city.
918.room_name: Samuel the Armourer glares at you.

919.name: Ra the Sun God~
description:
Ra is very bright!  It hurts your eyes to look at him, so you can tell little
about his appearance.  What you can tell, however, suggests that he is no one
to be trifled with.
919.room_name: Ra the Egyptian Sun God is resting here.

920.name: a chimera~
description:
This bizarre creature has three heads - one of a goat, one of a lion, and one
of a dragon.  It growls at you as you enter the cell, then suddenly attacks!

921.name: Hera~
description:
Hera, the wife of Zeus is here.  She smiles at you as you enter and invites you
to rest and sit for a while.

922.name: a roc~
description:
This is a giant bird.  It looks at you quizzically, then makes a noise and
looks away.

923.name: A citizen~
description: He looks happy and carefree.  He smiles and tips his hat to you.
923.room_name: A citizen of this town is strolling down the street here.

924.name: a pegasus~
description:
This horse is snow white with large wings.  Although it doesn't look very
threatening, it seems as though it would be dangerous if provoked.
924.room_name: A large horse with wings is here.

925.name: A Cook~
description: This man looks as is he has been spending WAY too much time in the kitchen.
925.room_name: A cook is here, hard at work.

926.name: The Jailer~
description:
He looks as though he has spent a lot of time underground, guarding the
prisoners.
926.room_name: The jailer is here, watching for intruders.

927.name: corridor guardian~
subroutines:
F for AHMV
F par ABCDEFGHIJK
M exall 901 0~

928.name: box watcher~
subroutines:
F for AHMV
F par ABCDEFGHIJK
M act 911 opens pandora~
M act 912 gets hope from pandora~
M random 903 10~
M grall 902 100~
928.room_name: ({WWizi{x) The Watcher of the Box stands here.

929.name: {yd{Ri{gsea{Rs{ye{x~
description:
This demon creature looks like a brown moth with a grotesquely
twisted humanoid face.  An aura of sickness permeates about it.

930.name: {cs{wo{Mrr{wo{cw{x~
description:
This demon creature looks like a brown moth with a grotesquely
twisted humanoid face.  An aura of despair permeates about it.

931.name: {8v{Ri{cc{8e{x~
description:
This demon creature looks like a brown moth with a grotesquely
twisted humanoid face.  An aura of malignant behaviour permeates about
it.

932.name: {Rmis{Yf{yortun{Ye{x~
description:
This demon creature looks like a brown moth with a grotesquely
twisted humanoid face.  An aura of bad luck permeates about it.
